..TEXT:
|Nel ventre tuo~... |fiore~: The flower, this rose,
was part of God's providential plan, as we know, and it is very
strikingly said to have germinated and blossomed in Mary's womb,
in the conception of Jesus.  The statement is made essentially in
terms of love, and the verb |raccese~ (rekindled) is used to
underscore the fact that God, following Adam's sin in the Garden
of Eden, withdrew his special love from the mass of mankind.
Cf., for the same great event, again in terms of love, the
metaphor of ^Purg.~ X, 41-42.
