..TEXT:
|Donna~: |Donna~ is here used with its full
etymological force of ^Domina~, as applied to the "Queen of
Heaven."  It will be noted that, beginning with this term of
address, three tercets now follow which exalt Mary to the
highest, from the point of view of mortal hope, and which precede
the specific grace implored in vss. 22-39, which terminate the
prayer.  |tanto vali~: "Thou dost so avail," i.e., in interceding
with God on the part of mortal sinners.
