..TEXT:
|E io~... |scarsi~: Bernard's phrasing |che mai
per mio veder non arsi~, with |arsi~ in the preterite, points
back to his own ardor, as a "contemplante," when on earth he
"burned" with the desire to have the experience in rapture which
he now implores for this living man.  See ^Par.~ XXXI, 111, and
n. to ^Par.~ XXXI, 110-111.  |prieghi~: The use of |prieghi~
here, then |priego~ in the next verse, followed by ^prieghi~ (vs.
32) and ^priego~ again (vs. 34) clearly builds up a sense of
ardor and urgency which Bernard puts into this his prayer to the
Queen of Heaven.  |scarsi~: "Insufficient."  Cf. ^Par.~ VII,
118.
..TCHR:
