|s@i che 'l sommo piacer~: |Piacer~ is here in the
objective focus, as frequently in the poem, beginning with
^Inf.~ V, 104.  It is now used in referring to God as the final
goal (cf. n. to vs. 27).  Other such phrasings may be recalled,
for example, ^Par.~ VIII, 87: ^l@a 've ogne ben si termina e
s'inizia.~  |li~ = ^gli.~  |si dispieghi~: "Be manifested to
him."  The manifesting will indeed prove to be a gradual
unfolding, which is the literal meaning of the verb ^dispiegare.~
