|ch$e la mia vista~... ^vera~ {v.54}: The action of
the poem is now entirely a matter of vision (|vista~), of ever
increasing vision, and of vision that is given from above,
through grace, a fact which |venendo~ stresses, for vision
^comes~ in this sense, and becomes ever clearer.  |sincera~:
"Pure."
