..TEXT:
|e pi@u e pi@u intrava per lo raggio~: The essential
nature of this last stretch of the journey is thus declared, from
the wayfarer's point of view.  He (i.e., his gaze) penetrates
(cf. ^Par.~ XXXII, 143) farther and farther upwards through the
descending light of glory, which sheds greater and greater grace
upon him (i.e., greater and greater revelation).  It is essential
to follow this double movement: upwards on the part of the mortal
man's seeing (penetration to the highest mystery) and downwards
on the part of the divine revelation (^venendo~, vs. 52).
