..TEXT:
|oltraggio~: The best gloss to the meaning here is
to be found in ^Par.~ I, 8: ^nostro intelletto si profonda
tanto.~  In older Italian, as Sapegno points out, |oltraggio~ did
not have the pejorative connotation that it has in modern usage.
(Cf. the English cognate ^outrage~ and the French ^outrance~, all
forms being based on the Latin ^ultra~, "beyond.")  The meaning
here is "excess," but only in the sense of ^profondarsi tanto~,
as above, and since this penetration was made possible by God, it
is not possible that the term should be pejorative: here there
can be no ^hubris~!
