..TEXT:
|Cos@i la neve~... ^Sibilla~ {v.66}: The theme of
"fade-out of vision" is conveyed by some of the most beautiful
verses in this ending of a great structure.  |si disigilla~:
"Unseals itself," "melts away," "loses its shape."  Cf.
^sigillare~ in the opposite sense of "giving form," ^Par.~ VII,
69.
