..TEXT:
|Io credo~... |aversi~: For a similar statement,
cf. ^Par.~ XXV, 118.  Dante is able to "endure" the brightness
of God's light of glory, a brightness increasing, as through it
he draws ever nearer to the vision face to face.  In vss. 100-102
we are to be told that it is not possible to turn away from this
light.  |aversi~: "Averted."
