..TEXT:
|tanto ch'i' giunsi~... |infinito~: The upward
movement through the ray of light has finally reached its goal,
as a verse numbered eighty-one declares!  (In medieval numerology
it is expected that the digits be added together, and nine is the
number of miracle, as every reader of the ^Vita nuova~ knows.)
|aspetto~: "Gaze."  |valore infinito~: God is thus named "the
Infinite Worth" as the journey in gazing attains to Him through
the light of glory by which He sees Himself.  See C. S. Singleton
(1958), pp. 20-23.
