..TEXT:
|Cos@i la mente mia~... |accesa~: The voice of the
narrator returns, in the past tense, as always, and the |cos@i~
returns the reader to the line of the narrative.  The verb
^mirare~, here stressed by repetition, can always connote
"marvel," as it does in this case, and for a moment now the
wayfarer remains "fixed" and "motionless" in his contemplation of
the marvel that is disclosed to him: God in His perfection, as
containing all things within Himself.  |faceasi~ = ^si faceva.~
|accesa~: "Kindled," with burning desire to see more and more.
