|Quella circulazion~... ^messo~ {v.132}: The
reader is now brought into the final focus of the poem, which is
on Christ, second person of the Trinity, as the phrases |s@i
concetta~ and ^lume reflesso~ make clear.  On the symbolical
implications of such a final focus, see C. S. Singleton (1969),
pp. 22-25.
