..TEXT:
|si convenne~: The verb expresses commensurability,
which is precisely the principle that makes the squaring of the
circle impossible, even for modern geometry.  And
incommensurability is at the heart of the mystery of the
Incarnation: how can the Word have become flesh, when Word
(divinity) and flesh are so incommensurate?
