..TEXT:
|ma non eran da ci@o le proprie penne~: Again the
metaphor of "wings," i.e., power for the upward flight to
complete vision of the where and the wherefore.  |Proprie penne~
underscores the aspect of the wayfarer's struggle in the
attainment of vision, which the poet continues to keep to the
fore, to the very end.
..TCHR:
