..TEXT:
|s@i come rota ch'igualmente @e mossa~: "The circle,
being the perfect figure, is an emblem of perfection; and
circular motion symbolizes full and faultless activity.  St.
Thomas, ^In Librum B. Dionysii De Divinis Nominibus~, Caput iv,
Lectio 7: `Et ideo circularitas motus animae completur in hoc
quod ad Deum manuducit'.  ['And therefore circularity completes
the movement of the soul in that it leads to God.']"  (Gr).
..TCHR:
415
